comments.content:
I sincerely appreciate all the feedback.

@Reetsde: You're point about being USB powered is an excellent one and very well received. I never thought about the power adapter. I'm all for reducing cable clutter.

@John Hudson/Reetsde/mk2: I'm currently borrowing a CanoScan and tried to scan directly from Photoshop with no luck. Back in the day, File\>Import\>Twain and away you went. However, with the CanoScan Toolbox, I have to use its interface and it will automatically open the image in Photoshop. Is this what you were referring to?

@James: I owned an Epson ink jet printer that I was really happy with until it finally stopped working. It served me very well and I have no complaints. I never really thought of them as being an option until you and mk2 suggested to look at them.
